g.text: Shimmering Wall of Vices: A colourful display of cigarettes and alcohol bottles lines the shop wall, inviting you closer.
Electrochemistry: Don't worry your pretty little head about it. Let's concentrate on what's IMPORTANT here.
You: "Okay. What will consuming this stuff do to my *body*?"
Frittte clerk: "Sure." She tilts her head back at the shelf. "So... are you going to buy anything, or...?"
Frittte clerk: "But I'm obliged to inform you that both alcohol and cigarettes damage your health. But I guess you already know that."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Of course not," the lieutenant says, glaring at you. "Frittte is an establishment that acts within the law. Is that all, detective?"
Electrochemistry: Bah! What's the point if they don't even sell the *good* drugs?
Frittte clerk: "Again, I'm obliged to inform you that both alcohol and cigarettes damage your health."
Frittte clerk: "You know..." She shrugs, uninterested in explaining it further.
Conceptualization: The beauty, the truth, the poetry of it all...
Volition: Don't ask, don't look, don't do *anything* here. Just go away. Get back to work.
Frittte clerk: "Um, the pale-aged vodka is special, I guess. It's stored in pale for a couple of years, which makes it super expensive and super strong."
You: (Say nothing. Just take it in.)
Frittte clerk: "Um... Sure. If you want something, I can get it for you. Just let me know and pay and stuff..." She adjusts her hat.
Electrochemistry: Know this -- you will never finish your alcohol *quest* if you don't buy beautiful alcohol.
Tutorial Agent: Use medication (like NOSAPHED and MAGNESIUM) to counteract the negative effects of substances. NOTE! Consuming substances can have unforeseen consequences for you.
Frittte clerk: "I'm obliged to inform you that both alcohol and cigarettes damage your health. But I guess you already know that."
Frittte clerk: "No." She fixes her hair underneath her cap. "Frittte only sells legal drugs, like the law says."
Perception (Sight): The bottles wink at you in the light. The smokes too glitter in their wrapping. It's like looking into a kind of heaven. Your knees are weak...
Electrochemistry: Good thing you're an *unrecovering* alcoholic then!
Frittte clerk: "Um... Guess not, no." She looks at the wall of goods behind her, then adjusts her hat.
You: "Do you sell speed at this establishment?"
You: "Please, tell me more about these products."
You: "I am in Heaven. I need it all so bad."

Tutorial Agent: Substances give powerful bonuses to your main stats, at the cost of damage to your Health or Morale. CIGARETTES raise your INTELLECT while damaging your Health, ALCOHOL raises PHYSIQUE while damaging your Morale.
Frittte clerk: "I'm obliged to inform you that both alcohol and cigarettes damage your health," she comments as you eye the goods behind her, "but I guess you already know that."
You: "Do you sell any... under the counter vices?"
You: "This is *not* a good place for a recovering addict."
Frittte clerk: "I mean, I already said it'd hurt you? I don't know what else they do." She stares at you, unsure.
Electrochemistry: There, in that dark green glass, a world of ruby, all in vain! The great flowing river of warmth: Wine-alcohol. Beer-alcohol. Love-alcohol.
Frittte clerk: "... Huh? Speed, like... *speed* speed? No, Frittte doesn't do that..." She blinks at you, bewildered.
